snippet.textDisplay:
His first ex-wife Patricia does look like Tisha. I saw them on a red carpet on tv in the late 90's when they were together and thought it was Tisha at first. I remember saying "They're married in real life?" That's how similar they looked. Even the way she was built back then. Even as a kid I saw a connection in that. He did love her from way back to House Party. He told her then if he ever got his own show he wanted her to be his girlfriend. She kind of brushed it off as him flirting and one day she got the call that Fox picked it up and he was serious. They both confirmed that in interviews. He had a thing for her bad, but she was already dating Duane Martin before Boomerang.

My theory:
Duane was also an actor, just not as prominent of an actor as Martin was, and then that show become a #1 hit show. His insecurities entered the picture knowing this other more famous guy adored her, now making her more successful an actress than her husband. She was now the bread winner. He became jealous and suspicious of their relationship, believing there was more than acting on set and that he was making passes at his wife when he wasn't around. He took legal action.
